## Introduction

Tailwind CSS has revolutionized the way we write CSS. Here are some best practices to get the most out of it.

## Use @apply Sparingly

While `@apply` is convenient, overusing it defeats the purpose of utility-first CSS:

```css
/* Avoid this */
.btn {
  @apply px-4 py-2 bg-blue-500 text-white rounded;
}

/* Prefer this */
<button class="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-500 text-white rounded">Click me</button>
```

## Configure Your Theme

Customize Tailwind's default theme to match your design system:

```javascript
// tailwind.config.js
module.exports = {
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        brand: {
          primary: '#1a202c',
          secondary: '#2d3748',
        },
      },
    },
  },
}
```

## Use Component Libraries Wisely

Component libraries like Skeleton UI can accelerate development, but ensure they align with your design needs.

## PurgeCSS Configuration

Always configure PurgeCSS properly to remove unused styles in production:

```javascript
module.exports = {
  content: ['./src/**/*.{html,js,svelte,ts}'],
}
```

## Conclusion

Following these best practices will help you build maintainable and performant applications with Tailwind CSS.
